---
/**
 * idempotency-keys-deep-dive · Figure 6 — a key guards one boundary, not a chain
 * (Level 5; the exactly-once = at-least-once + idempotent endpoint frame).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/distributed-systems/idempotency-keys-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). The one arrowhead marker it references
 * (#arw via marker-end="url(#arw)") is inlined here in a local <defs> so it
 * resolves standalone (verbatim from the source's hidden top-of-body defs).
 * Lives as an .astro component because raw inline SVG with kebab-case attrs is
 * unreliable inside MDX.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 200"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A key guards one operation against one store; a chain of three services needs three independent idempotency guards, one per hop"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="280"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">a key guards ONE boundary — not a chain</text
            >
            <rect x="18" y="44" width="120" height="46" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text
                x="78"
                y="66"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">service A</text
            >
            <text x="78" y="81" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">key #1</text>
            <rect x="220" y="44" width="120" height="46" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text
                x="280"
                y="66"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">service B</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="81" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">key #2</text>
            <rect x="422" y="44" width="120" height="46" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text
                x="482"
                y="66"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">service C</text
            >
            <text x="482" y="81" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">key #3</text>
            <line x1="138" y1="67" x2="218" y2="67" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line x1="340" y1="67" x2="420" y2="67" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <text x="178" y="58" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">own dedup</text
            >
            <text x="380" y="58" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">own dedup</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >each hop needs its own idempotency — NOT a distributed-transaction substitute</text
            >
            <!-- exactly once -->
            <rect x="60" y="134" width="440" height="52" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="280"
                y="154"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#244a2e"
                >exactly-once EFFECT = at-least-once delivery + idempotent / dedup endpoint</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="172" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >the key is just the most common way to BE that endpoint — move dedup to the
                receiver if the sender can't be safe</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The whole topic in one frame: there is no exactly-once delivery; there is at-least-once + an
        idempotent receiver. The key is one way to be that receiver.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
